```latex
\documentclass{standalone}
\usepackage{tikz}

\begin{document}
\begin{tikzpicture}[scale=2]
    % Draw the grid lines
    \draw (0,0) -- (3,0);
    \draw (0,1) -- (3,1);
    \draw (0,2) -- (3,2);
    \draw (0,0) -- (0,3);
    \draw (1,0) -- (1,3);
    \draw (2,0) -- (2,3);

    % Define the positions for X and O
    \node at (0.5, 2.5) {X};
    \node at (1.5, 2.5) {O};
    \node at (2.5, 2.5) {X};
    \node at (0.5, 1.5) {O};
    \node at (1.5, 1.5) {};
    \node at (2.5, 1.5) {X};
    \node at (0.5, 0.5) {O};
    \node at (1.5, 0.5) {};
    \node at (2.5, 0.5) {};

    % Highlight the winning hyperedges
    \draw[thick, red] (0,0) rectangle (1,1); % Top-left diagonal
    \draw[thick, red] (2,0) rectangle (3,1); % Top-right diagonal

\end{tikzpicture}
\end{document}
```

### Explanation:
- **Grid Lines**: The `draw` commands create the horizontal and vertical lines that form the \(3 \times 3\) board.
- **Positions for X and O**: Nodes are placed at specific coordinates to represent the players' moves.
- **Winning Hyperedges**: Red rectangles highlight the winning hyperedges (diagonals in this case).

